<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
    MG-42 caliber unification with Parabellum.

    When Parabellum is loaded, redirect the RH2 RN MG-42 GPMG to share
    Parabellum's AmmoSet_8mmM (their 7.92x57mm Mauser implementation,
    used by ~10 Parabellum weapons including stationary MGs). Both mods
    represent the same real-world caliber but bundle their own def names,
    creating two parallel ammo pools where there should be one.

    Parabellum's AmmoSet_8mmM ammo types:
      Ammo_8mmM_SP  (FMJ - standard ball)
      Ammo_8mmM_KP  (AP - armor-piercing)
      Ammo_8mmM_BP  (HE-Tracer)
      Ammo_8mmM_P88M (special)

    Wrapped in PatchOperationFindMod so it no-ops when Parabellum isn't
    active (MG-42 keeps its RH2-bundled AmmoSet_792x57mmMauser in that case).

    Per Kirkiness's request - 7.92x57 is historically the correct MG-42
    caliber, and unifying ammo pools means colonies don't need to stockpile
    two parallel 7.92x57 inventories.
-->
<Patch>
    <Operation Class="PatchOperationFindMod">
        <mods>
            <li>Parabellum</li>
        </mods>
        <match Class="PatchOperationSequence">
            <operations>
                <li Class="PatchOperationReplace">
                    <xpath>Defs/ThingDef[defName="RNGun_MG42_GPMG"]/verbs/li[verbClass="CombatExtended.Verb_ShootCE"]/defaultProjectile</xpath>
                    <value>
                        <defaultProjectile>Bullet_8mmM_SP</defaultProjectile>
                    </value>
                </li>
                <li Class="PatchOperationReplace">
                    <xpath>Defs/ThingDef[defName="RNGun_MG42_GPMG"]/comps/li[@Class="CombatExtended.CompProperties_AmmoUser"]/ammoSet</xpath>
                    <value>
                        <ammoSet>AmmoSet_8mmM</ammoSet>
                    </value>
                </li>
            </operations>
        </match>
    </Operation>
</Patch>
